President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Mark Cohen is nominated for Member of the Merit Systems Protection Board and will be designated Vice Chairman. G. Kathleen Hill is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Malta. Lynne Benioff, Paula Robinson Collins, Nicola Miner, and Janet Reilly are appointed as members of the Board of Directors of the Presidio Trust. Eric Ortner is appointed as a member of the President's Committee on the Arts and the Humanities. Shervin Pishevar is appointed as a member of the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. Steven Spinner is appointed as a member of the President's Commission on White House Fellowships. President Obama expressed his pleasure in working with these individuals, stating that they are experienced and committed to serving the country.